&lt;p&gt;Detailed drawings/full particulars of the proposed development showing the matters set out below must be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority, in writing, prior to the commencement of the relevant part of works. The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the details thus approved which shall be implemented in full prior to the first use of the development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

a) Detailed elevation and sectional plans of all replacement windows showing a thickness of glass of 12mm, integrated glazing bars and a putty finish.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
b) Detail of the lead material to be used in the rear dormer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

REASON: To ensure the development integrates with the host building and surrounding conservation area.&lt;/p&gt;
